The paper deals with distributed graph algorithms, which typically fall under the categories of Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The focus on randomized and deterministic algorithms suggests a connection to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the specific problems addressed in the paper, such as hypergraph matching and Lov\'{a}sz Local Lemma, suggest a connection to Graph Theory (cs.GT).
